We recommended the following to the Management,
a Demand immediate settlement/liquidation of the outstanding cash advances of the OIC-Municipal Treasurer pursuant to COA Circular No. 97-002;
b. Require the Municipal Accountant to strictly monitor the grant and liquidation of cash advances and avoid granting additional CAs unless the previous cash advance is first settled or a proper accounting thereof is made pursuant to Section 89 of PD No. 1445;
c. Conduct regular reconciliation of accounts between the cashbooks of the accountable officer and books of accounts maintained by the Accounting Office; and
d. Institute appropriate administrative and/or legal action against the accountable officer for the immediate setilement of these cash advances.
